1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,253
- Why would my son do that to your father?
- [pensive music playing]

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:05,171
[Jamilah] <i>The video is real.</i>

3
00:00:05,255 --> 00:00:09,050
But I know Marcus
did that to protect Father.

4
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:10,802
[Espina] <i>That's why</i>
<i>they released that video.</i>

5
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:12,554
Because Marcus is a major threat to them.

6
00:00:12,637 --> 00:00:13,680
We have to act.

7
00:00:13,763 --> 00:00:15,432
We can't just sit around doing nothing!

8
00:00:15,515 --> 00:00:19,102
[Espina] <i>The people</i>
<i>we're up against are powerful.</i>

9
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:22,522
You can't help Marcus
if you're in danger too.

10
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:24,983
[Manuel] <i>I thought you were good.</i>

11
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:29,571
Why couldn't you catch Marcus Reyes?

12
00:00:29,654 --> 00:00:34,159
Why are you all so convinced
Reyes is the culprit?

13
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:35,869
[Espina] <i>Just because of one video?</i>

14
00:00:35,952 --> 00:00:39,247
[in English] Agent Reyes,
you are hereby placed

15
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,791
under preventive suspension.

16
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:44,669
[in English] Effective immediately.

17
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:46,212
[Marcus] <i>Even if</i>
<i>they remove me from service,</i>

18
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:48,256
I'll still finish what we started.

19
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:51,384
[Lara] <i>Because of you, Marcus,</i>
<i>Dad lost faith in me.</i>

20
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:54,763
[in English] You deserve this, Marcus.
You deserve this.

21
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:56,514
[Marcus] <i>While I'm out of service,</i>

22
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:59,684
<i>Major Allan Espina will serve</i>
<i>as your team leader.</i>

23
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:01,561
[in English] He's not even a part of TFA.

24
00:01:01,644 --> 00:01:04,898
And if we're talking about
experience and credentials,

25
00:01:04,981 --> 00:01:07,692
Major Espina is more than capable
of leading a team.

26
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:10,236
I have no problem taking command
from Major Espina.

27
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,988
- No problem on my end.
- Same here, ma'am.

28
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:12,864
Me too.

29
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:14,240
[Lara] <i>Marcus doesn't trust me.</i>

30
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:16,201
[in English] <i>He's even</i>
<i>being vocal about it.</i>

31
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:17,744
[Lara] <i>How am I supposed to control him</i>

32
00:01:17,827 --> 00:01:19,204
if he doesn't trust me?

33
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:22,832
What you should do
is get close to Task Force Alpha.

34
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,293
<i>They're the ones you need to manipulate,</i>

35
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:26,503
<i>not Marcus.</i>

36
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:38,348
[mysterious theme music playing]

37
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,695
[pensive music playing]

38
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:58,451
[knock on door]

39
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,287
[Lara] Major Espina?

40
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,124
- [door clicks shut]
- What is it, Agent Angeles?

41
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,877
[in English] Listen, we got off
on the wrong foot.

42
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,754
But we've got too many problems right now.

43
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:11,631
[in English] We can't
be uncoordinated as a team.

44
00:02:11,714 --> 00:02:14,759
So, if Agent Reyes trusts you,

45
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:17,053
then I'm willing to work with you.

46
00:02:19,889 --> 00:02:22,308
Looks like we want
the same thing, Agent Angeles.

47
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:25,019
[in English] Good. I'm glad to hear
we're on the same page.

48
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,314
I'm just curious how you and Agent Reyes

49
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:29,440
managed to get along.

50
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:32,235
You used to clash, even during missions.

51
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,864
And now he entrusted
Task Force Alpha to you.

52
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:38,783
[tense sting]

53
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:41,494
We just had a serious talk.

54
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:43,955
Maybe that's how it is at first.

55
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:47,834
Conflict is unavoidable, isn't it?

56
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:48,751
Mm-hmm.

57
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,753
[Espina] Just like us, Agent Angeles.

58
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:55,758
But now we've gotten
to know each other better.

59
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:58,845
I hope the same happens with us.

60
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:01,306
[in English] We'll see.

61
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:09,731
Agent Angeles, I'm not your enemy.

62
00:03:10,815 --> 00:03:13,902
But there are enemies all around us.

63
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:17,780
So I hope we can work together
to find them.

64
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:21,784
[in English] Sure. I agree.

65
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:23,786
Good.

66
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,164
I hope we can get along.

67
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:27,498
I hope so too.

68
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:33,630
They're trying to silence me.

69
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:36,299
I can feel they're getting scared,
which means…

70
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:39,427
I'm getting closer to the truth.

71
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:42,680
That's why I can't stop now, Mom.

72
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,224
- [pensive music playing]
- [breathes deeply]

73
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:46,351
But son, what else are they capable of?

74
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,478
You've already been suspended.

75
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:51,397
What will they do next
if you still don't stop?

76
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:53,775
How far will they go to silence you?

77
00:03:53,858 --> 00:03:56,486
Mom, I can protect myself.

78
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:57,820
You know that.

79
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,864
Don't worry, okay?

80
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,324
But son…

81
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:04,160
Mom, whatever I'm doing right now,

82
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,746
I know I'm doing the right thing.

83
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:09,415
My enemies have done too much harm.

84
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:12,669
Too many families are demanding justice.

85
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,629
They've wronged too many people.

86
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:17,548
They deserve that justice, Mom.

87
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,842
If I give up now,

88
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:23,388
no one may be able to stop them.

89
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:28,268
Looks like you've already
made up your mind.

90
00:04:30,061 --> 00:04:35,525
All I can do now is pray to God
for your safety, son.

91
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:41,114
[music intensifies]

92
00:04:41,197 --> 00:04:42,991
May Allah guide you.

93
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:49,622
<i>So what's really going on?</i>

94
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:53,793
<i>Did Agent Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>really rescue Datu Rahman</i>

95
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:55,336
<i>from the NLEA?</i>

96
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:58,256
<i>Has that organization become so corrupt</i>

97
00:04:58,339 --> 00:05:01,509
<i>that even its leaders are divided?</i>

98
00:05:01,592 --> 00:05:05,888
<i>But even if the intention was good,</i>

99
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:08,057
<i>does that justify the means?</i>

100
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:13,187
<i>No matter how I look at it,</i>

101
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:16,107
<i>what you did was still illegal,</i>
<i>Marcus Reyes.</i>

102
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:18,192
<i>It's still illegal.</i>

103
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:20,570
The problem with our country

104
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:23,489
is that the people who enforce the law

105
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:25,241
are often the first to break it.

106
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:28,703
Why is Marcus Reyes hiding Datu Rahman?

107
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:33,833
Why is he risking his life
and career for him?

108
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:37,587
<i>Could he be the traitor within the NLEA?</i>

109
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:40,840
<i>This is getting crazier and crazier.</i>
<i>So much is happening.</i>

110
00:05:40,923 --> 00:05:42,759
<i>So many plot twists!</i>

111
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:44,886
- <i>Seriously, it's insane.</i>
- <i>True!</i>

112
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:46,471
- <i>Right?</i>
- <i>It's like a soap opera!</i>

113
00:05:46,554 --> 00:05:47,388
<i>Exactly.</i>

114
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:50,892
<i>Is it true, the gossip</i>
<i>about that handsome cop?</i>

115
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,602
- [man] Who?
- <i>Marcus Reyes.</i>

116
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:55,229
- <i>Oh yeah, Marcus Reyes.</i>
- <i>Wait a second, Mama Loi.</i>

117
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:58,274
<i>You mean the thing</i>
<i>about hiding Datu Rahman?</i>

118
00:05:58,357 --> 00:05:59,484
<i>Yeah.</i>

119
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,737
- <i>But why would he do that?</i>
- <i>Exactly!</i>

120
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:05,740
<i>There are so many issues right now!</i>

121
00:06:05,823 --> 00:06:09,327
<i>The public has so many questions.</i>

122
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:14,207
<i>Will we hear a statement</i>
<i>from Marcus Reyes?</i>

123
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:16,542
<i>Is he really telling the truth?</i>

124
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:19,295
<i>Will he be held accountable</i>
<i>for what he did?</i>

125
00:06:19,837 --> 00:06:22,006
<i>What do you think, Mrena?</i>

126
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,633
<i>I don't feel good about this.</i>

127
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:26,010
- <i>What about you, Mama Loi?</i>
- <i>Oh, sis.</i>

128
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:27,970
<i>Let's stay out of it.</i>
<i>We might get involved.</i>

129
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:30,973
<i>Then why are we talking</i>
<i>about it on the show?</i>

130
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:33,226
- <i>You're not giving us anything!</i>
- <i>No!</i>

131
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:35,144
- <i>You're the one who started it!</i>
- <i>Me?</i>

132
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,938
- <i>Yes.</i>
- <i>Yes.</i>

133
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:38,231
<i>We might get dragged into this.</i>

134
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,817
[Ethan] This is all
we managed to recover, sir.

135
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:45,029
The rest are completely damaged.

136
00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:48,991
But we'll see if we can recover
the other files,

137
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,910
including the encrypted ones.

138
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:53,746
They cleaned everything up fast.

139
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:57,375
But you can handle this.

140
00:06:57,458 --> 00:06:59,168
I saw your credentials.

141
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,170
Come on, sir.

142
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:02,797
What do you think I am, a hacker?

143
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:07,969
I mean, not anymore.
I left that life behind.

144
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:10,430
I know you can do this, right?

145
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:14,267
Yes, sir, but this is tough.

146
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:16,352
Still, I can handle it.

147
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,479
- I'll get it done.
- You can do it.

148
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,445
[motorcycle engine whirring]

149
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:29,323
[Gracia] Why do you look so serious?

150
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:31,993
Gracia?

151
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:35,872
You look really serious. Are you okay?

152
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:37,748
It's nothing.

153
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:40,918
It's our leader, Sir Marcus.

154
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:42,170
He's been suspended.

155
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:44,380
I saw the video.

156
00:07:45,089 --> 00:07:47,508
I hope he's okay.

157
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,093
I hope so too.

158
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:51,429
The world's such a mess right now.

159
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:52,346
It really is.

160
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:56,392
Good thing… you're here to save me.

161
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:58,603
Don't worry.

162
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:00,938
I'll always save you.

163
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:07,278
[gentle music playing]

164
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:08,488
You know,

165
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:12,241
this is the first time we've had
a conversation this peaceful.

166
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:17,455
No pickpockets, no hostage-takers,

167
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:20,333
and nobody getting shot.

168
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:22,710
You're right.

169
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:24,921
It's nice and quiet.

170
00:08:27,131 --> 00:08:29,050
What's wrong?

171
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:30,134
Oh no.

172
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:34,722
What if what happened to me happens again?

173
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:36,516
Would you still save me?

174
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:38,601
Now I'm scared to go home.

175
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:39,936
Maybe you should walk me home.

176
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:41,395
[Andre chuckles]

177
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:42,563
Uh…

178
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:45,650
Sure. Where do you live?

179
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:48,402
Come on, I was joking.

180
00:08:49,278 --> 00:08:52,240
I'm from Parañaque. How about you?

181
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,450
Commonwealth.

182
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,993
Damn.

183
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:57,912
That's so far away!

184
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:58,955
Never mind.

185
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:01,374
I should get going.

186
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:02,708
Bye-bye!

187
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,168
Sir!

188
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:16,347
I'll go with you.

189
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:18,224
Why are you coming with me?

190
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:19,600
I'll take you home.

191
00:09:19,684 --> 00:09:21,352
I said you don't have to.

192
00:09:21,435 --> 00:09:22,436
It's okay.

193
00:09:24,438 --> 00:09:26,732
Usman, I want this to be over.

194
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:30,486
I'm tired of pretending.
I'm tired of lying.

195
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:34,031
But I do it every day, every minute.

196
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,575
I don't want to keep pretending.

197
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,077
Especially now that

198
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,329
Marcus has become my friend.

199
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:45,001
[morose music playing]

200
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:46,711
[Usman] I feel the same way, Jalil.

201
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:49,964
As long as I keep hiding
your true identity from Marcus,

202
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:53,551
I feel like I'm betraying my friend.

203
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:56,512
But our mission with Mustapha
isn't over yet.

204
00:09:57,346 --> 00:10:01,142
And justice hasn't yet
been served for my neighbors.

205
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:03,311
Usman, I'm not going to let them down.

206
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:07,023
I need to find out
who is really responsible

207
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,899
for their deaths,

208
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:11,861
so they cannot harm others again.

209
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:14,113
I have to finish this.

210
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,116
[Usman] I understand.

211
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:19,910
They have to pay for all of this,

212
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:21,495
so that it comes to an end.

213
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:25,875
[in English] The Japanese delegates
will be escorted

214
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:28,336
by our elite team, Task Force Alpha.

215
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:29,837
[thrilling music playing]

216
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:30,921
[key clacks]

217
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:35,593
We will station security
at every strategic point

218
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:37,595
to ensure the safety of every attendee.

219
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:42,475
Every day, we are sweeping the area
for any potential threats.

220
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,895
[in English] Wow! This is very thorough.

221
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:48,981
[in English] Colonel Solares,
General Carillo,

222
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:51,859
I am very impressed.

223
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:54,153
We did not make the mistake
of trusting you.

224
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:55,321
[Manuel chuckles]

225
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:59,575
Of course. For the progress of our country

226
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:02,912
and to make the vision
of a new Philippines possible,

227
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:04,246
I will do anything.

228
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:07,291
[chuckling, in English] Of course.
Thank you.

229
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,211
- General.
- Thank you.

230
00:11:11,128 --> 00:11:12,296
- [in English] Thank you.
- Colonel.

231
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,882
[man 1, in English] I just have
a few questions for you here,

232
00:11:14,965 --> 00:11:17,134
but I'll let you address them
some other time.

233
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:18,427
- [man 2, in English] Okay, sir.
- [man 1, in English] Thank you.

234
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:22,890
[music intensifies]

235
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:29,063
We will consolidate
the resources of the police

236
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:33,317
and focus them in a single area.

237
00:11:33,401 --> 00:11:34,276
[snickers]

238
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,405
[in English] They won't even know
what's coming.

239
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:40,116
[both snickering]

240
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,580
[music intensifies]

241
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:47,665
[music fades]

242
00:11:47,748 --> 00:11:48,874
[knock on door]

243
00:11:57,174 --> 00:11:58,175
Suarez.

244
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:00,678
Sir, did you hear?

245
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:02,555
[tense music playing]

246
00:12:02,638 --> 00:12:04,682
The verdict for Sir Marcus
will be delivered tomorrow.

247
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:06,267
Why's it happening so soon?

248
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:08,811
I have a bad feeling about this.

249
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:19,196
The generals will announce
their decision tomorrow, Ma.

250
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:21,031
I don't know how to feel.

251
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:23,242
If I'm removed from service…

252
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:25,995
- [breathes deeply]
- [morose music playing]

253
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:29,165
…it will take me longer
to finish my mission,

254
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:32,585
and more people will fall victim.

255
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:34,295
[somber music playing]

256
00:12:34,378 --> 00:12:38,048
I feel like Gabriel
will be disappointed in me.

257
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:41,135
That's not true, son.

258
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:44,680
You've saved a lot of people.

259
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:48,309
You've overcome every challenge
by being strong.

260
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:51,353
Believe in yourself.

261
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:54,523
Don't let those bastards bring you down.

262
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:55,543
[glass thuds]

263
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:15,938
[glass shatters]

264
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:28,951
[Ahmad] <i>They want</i>
<i>to silence you, Agent Reyes.</i>

265
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:31,203
<i>That can only mean</i>

266
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:33,581
<i>they're beginning to feel afraid.</i>

267
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:45,050
[pensive music playing]

268
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:53,225
[Ahmad] <i>Every move</i>
<i>is too carefully planned.</i>

269
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,519
<i>Too flawless.</i>

270
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:57,980
<i>This means</i>

271
00:14:58,689 --> 00:15:03,027
<i>that a single hand</i>
<i>is directing all of you.</i>

272
00:15:04,778 --> 00:15:06,947
<i>Sowing chaos.</i>

273
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:13,537
Which one of you
is the mastermind behind all this?

274
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:15,748
Which one of you

275
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:19,126
is pulling strings from the shadows?

276
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:22,880
[In Arabic] You are our Protector,
so help us,

277
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:24,965
give us victory against
the disbelieving people.

278
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:28,344
[In Arabic] God is great.

279
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:33,557
[pensive music playing]

280
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:52,284
I thought you were competent,

281
00:15:52,368 --> 00:15:57,164
which is why the Muslim Affairs office
stationed you here.

282
00:15:58,165 --> 00:15:59,625
But…

283
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:04,463
why didn't you arrest Marcus Reyes

284
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:10,469
when all along he was hiding Datu Rahman?

285
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:08,277
You've committed
countless violations, Reyes,

286
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:11,905
illegal detention, kidnapping,

287
00:17:11,989 --> 00:17:13,615
and yet you have the audacity to accuse

288
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:16,910
your fellow police officers
when you're the one engaged

289
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:18,328
in misconduct?

290
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,123
You're the traitor here.

291
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:26,003
[Manuel] I never imagined

292
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:30,215
that it would be you
disgracing this agency.

293
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,260
[sighs] How disappointing.

294
00:17:35,679 --> 00:17:37,723
[Marcus] <i>For something to happen,</i>

295
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,267
<i>three things are needed.</i>

296
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,643
<i>Ability,</i>

297
00:17:42,269 --> 00:17:45,147
<i>opportunity, and motivation.</i>

298
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:47,983
<i>General Carillo.</i>

299
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:51,945
<i>You're one of the most influential people</i>

300
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:54,531
<i>in all of NLEA and SID.</i>

301
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:58,660
<i>So if you're the one</i>
<i>behind all this chaos,</i>

302
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:02,664
<i>it's no wonder you can pull it off.</i>

303
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:07,002
<i>You have both the ability</i>
<i>and the opportunity.</i>

304
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:09,755
<i>But why?</i>

305
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:13,509
<i>What's your motivation?</i>

306
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:20,307
[pensive music playing]

307
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:23,310
[Jalil] <i>Are you, General Carillo,</i>

308
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:26,188
<i>truly the mastermind behind all this?</i>

309
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:29,108
<i>And if you really are,</i>

310
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:31,652
<i>why are you doing it?</i>

311
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,162
[thrilling music playing]

312
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:44,039
<i>You, Lara,</i>

313
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:49,336
<i>are my way of finding the answers</i>
<i>to my questions.</i>

314
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:58,554
[gloomy music playing]

315
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:09,982
[music intensifying]

316
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:11,817
- [music ends]
- [man, in English] Yes, alright.

317
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:18,824
[dramatic tense music playing]

318
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:23,704
- Sir, I found something.
- Come in.

319
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:28,625
I was able to recover paper trails
from encrypted files.

320
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:34,047
[Jalil] Those are bank transactions.

321
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:35,674
[Ethan] That's right, sir.
And listen to this.

322
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:39,428
The total cash flow of this bank account

323
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:41,638
has reached 870 million pesos.

324
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:44,016
Find out who owns this account.

325
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:45,267
[Ethan] Yes, sir.

326
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:48,812
- [digital trilling]
- I got it, sir.

327
00:19:48,896 --> 00:19:50,314
[dramatic tense music playing]

328
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,484
Who is the owner of this company?

329
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,784
[digital trilling]

330
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:04,661
Sir, this is a shell company.

331
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,955
The officers listed are dummies.

332
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:10,959
This is where their money
would pass through

333
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:13,587
before finally transferring
to their own personal accounts.

334
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,381
What are you doing?

335
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:19,801
I'm just looking for…

336
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:21,386
- this!
- [digital trilling]

337
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:25,140
These are just bank transactions, sir.

338
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:28,644
But this one…
They bought land and a house.

339
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,815
[Espina] Colonel Luis del Mundo.

340
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:36,026
[gunshot]

341
00:20:38,862 --> 00:20:40,364
When's the last transaction he made?

342
00:20:41,031 --> 00:20:42,032
Let me check, sir.

343
00:20:42,115 --> 00:20:43,158
It's last week.

344
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:45,786
His account is still active.

345
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:48,747
Sir, check this out.

346
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:52,251
The fleet schedule of this company

347
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:54,211
is still going 'til now.

348
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:57,089
This one's scheduled

349
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:58,840
to go in 36 minutes.

350
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,554
[line ringing]

351
00:21:04,638 --> 00:21:07,391
Agent Angeles. I need your help.

352
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:11,520
[keyboard clacking]

353
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:12,521
Sir!

354
00:21:13,438 --> 00:21:14,940
Why? What's going on?

355
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:17,192
Major Espina said we have an operation.

356
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:18,360
[Sean] Come on?

357
00:21:18,443 --> 00:21:20,028
- [in English] Let's go! Let's go!
- [in English] Let's go.

358
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:31,248
[keyboard clacking]

359
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,424
[beeping]

360
00:21:40,507 --> 00:21:41,925
- [in English] Here. Zoom in.
- [Buster] Copy, ma'am.

361
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,927
[beeping]

362
00:21:45,929 --> 00:21:50,767
[rapid beeping]

363
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:52,352
Espina.

364
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:53,770
[Lara] <i>We've traced them.</i>

365
00:21:54,896 --> 00:21:56,481
[in English] Black SUV.

366
00:21:56,565 --> 00:21:59,109
[in English] Plate number, VNC-1188.

367
00:21:59,192 --> 00:22:01,903
Heading northbound. They're
on their way to an abandoned building

368
00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:03,697
at the corner of Kalantiaw
and Tasaday Street.

369
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:06,199
[in English] That's where the target
is going. You have three minutes.

370
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:07,159
[in English] Copy.

371
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:13,373
Usman, turn right here.

372
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:14,833
[in English] Copy, sir.

373
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:42,235
[suspenseful music playing]

374
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,572
[in English] Agent Angeles,
we are in position.

375
00:22:45,655 --> 00:22:46,698
[radio static]

376
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:50,327
- [digital trilling]
- [keyboard clacking]

377
00:22:57,292 --> 00:22:59,669
They're on their way to you. They're near.

378
00:22:59,753 --> 00:23:00,712
[in English] Copy.

379
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:16,812
[in English] Base. Target spotted.

380
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:18,980
[Espina, in English] <i>Thirty meters.</i>

381
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:20,148
[in English] <i>Twenty meters.</i>

382
00:23:21,358 --> 00:23:23,151
[in English] Go! Go! Go!

383
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:25,362
- [tires screeching]
- [indistinct]

384
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:26,530
- [man] Get out!
- [Espina] Get out of the car!

385
00:23:26,613 --> 00:23:27,656
- [man 1] We're the police!
- [man 2] Police.

386
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:29,032
- [Espina] Get out!
- [Felix] Put your hands up!

387
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:30,951
- [man 2] We're the police!
- [Felix] Get out of the vehicle!

388
00:23:31,034 --> 00:23:32,160
- [officer] Get out!
- [Espina] Get out!

389
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:33,453
[Felix] Get out!

390
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:36,331
- [man 1] We're the police!
- [officer] Face here!

391
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:40,627
[tense music playing]

392
00:23:44,422 --> 00:23:45,257
‪[inaudible]

393
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:58,728
[cases rattling]

394
00:24:04,317 --> 00:24:05,861
[suspenseful sting]

395
00:24:08,613 --> 00:24:09,447
‪[digital trilling]

396
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:26,590
[dramatic music playing]

397
00:24:34,347 --> 00:24:36,766
- Can I play with you guys?
- [tense music playing]

398
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:38,435
What's that on your head?

399
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:39,895
Take it off, will you?!

400
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:40,770
Hey, don't!

401
00:24:40,854 --> 00:24:42,981
We call this headpiece hijab.

402
00:24:43,064 --> 00:24:44,191
In our religion, Islam,

403
00:24:44,274 --> 00:24:48,153
we wear this to show our respect

404
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:50,739
and commitment to our faith.

405
00:24:50,822 --> 00:24:52,574
We will now announce our judgment.

406
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:55,619
If you're going to fire Agent Reyes,
you should fire me as well.

407
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:58,288
The judgment hasn't been given yet,
but we've already won.

408
00:24:58,371 --> 00:25:01,499
[Usman] How shameful! To think
our fellow officers are behind this!

409
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:02,709
[in English] Congratulations, team.

410
00:25:02,792 --> 00:25:04,377
I heard it was a mission accomplished.

411
00:25:04,461 --> 00:25:05,378
[in English] Congratulations.

412
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:06,755
[man] Are you here to say goodbye, sir?

413
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:08,465
[man] Come on, sir!
We won't let that happen!

414
00:25:08,548 --> 00:25:10,550
[tense music playing]

415
00:25:10,634 --> 00:25:13,178
If you have any trouble
hitching a ride, give me a call.

416
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:15,138
I'll have Marcus pick you up.

417
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:17,057
- I--
- Oh, Doc! Jamilah really likes hi--

418
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:19,809
Oh, no! We'll be fine, Doc!

419
00:25:19,893 --> 00:25:20,894
[man] <i>Sir.</i>

420
00:25:20,977 --> 00:25:23,730
<i>I found the woman you've been watching.</i>

421
00:25:24,564 --> 00:25:25,941
<i>She's Jamilah Abubakar.</i>

422
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:30,362
[Felix] I can finally get my revenge
on you, Jalil Abubakar.

423
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:32,781
[laughing maniacally]

424
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:35,408
[music fades]
